GPC3


Description

Glypican-3 (GPC3). Cell surface proteoglycan that bears heparan sulfate. Used as a marker for hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC). When attached to the cell surface, stimulates the growth of HCC cells by increasing canonical Wnt signaling.
